'''Yudh''' is an upcoming [[Indian television]] mini series directed by [[Anurag Kashyap]] starring actor [[Amitabh Bachchan]] in the lead role. <ref name=a>{{cite news|title=Yudh to replace Bade Achhe Lagte Hain|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/television/yudh-to-replace-bade-achhe-lagte-hain/article1-1236645.aspx|accessdate=6 July 2014|publisher=Hindustan Times|date=4 July 2014}}</ref><ref name="ix">{{cite news|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/television/watch-amitabh-bachchan-battles-world-himself-in-tv-show-yudh/|title=Amitabh Bachchan battles world, himself in TV show <U+2018>Yudh<U+2019>|date=2 May 2014|publisher=The Indian Express}}</ref> It also stars veteran actors like [[Nawazuddin Siddiqui]], [[Sarika]] and [[Kay Kay Menon|Kay Kay Menon]].<ref name=a/> This show is Amitabh Bachchan's debut fiction television show .<ref name=a/><ref>{{Cite news|url = http://ibnlive.in.com/news/amitabh-bachchans-debut-tv-series-yudh-to-go-on-air-in-july/477506-44-124.html|title = Amitabh Bachchan's debut TV series 'Yudh' to go on air in July|last = |first = IANS|date = 8 June 2014|work = |accessdate = 6 July 2014|publisher = ibnlive.in}}</ref> Produced by [[Endemol India]] and Saraswati Creations, ''Yudh'' is scheduled to premier on [[Sony Entertainment Television (India)|Sony Entertainment Television India]] on 14 July 2014.<ref name=a/> ''Yudh'' replaced the soap opera ''[[Bade Achhe Lagte Hain]]'', produced by the [[Balaji Telefilms]], which had been on air since 2011.<ref name=a/>

==Plot==
Yudhisthir Sikhawar, an elite businessman has a neuropsychological disorder. He is now caught in a battle with himself and his health, an emotional battle with his family and a corporate battle with his rivals.

